<item>
            <title>[SPARK-34064] Broadcast job is not aborted even the SQL statement canceled</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-34064</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-27036&quot; title=&quot;Even Broadcast thread is timed out, BroadCast Job is not aborted.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-27036&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-27036&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced a runId for BroadcastExchangeExec to resolve the problem that a broadcast job is not aborted when broadcast timeout happens. Since the runId is a random UUID, when a SQL statement is cancelled, these broadcast sub-jobs still not canceled as a whole.&lt;/p&gt;

